Whatis database
***************

   The @{b}makewhatis.pl@{ub} perl script extracts the name and a short
description from unformatted manpages and creates the @{b}whatis@{ub} database
file @{b}whatis.db@{ub}. @{b}makewhatis.pl@{ub} can read gzip'ed manpages.


 @{" makewhatis.pl options      " link "makewhatis.pl options"}  Options for makewhatis.pl.
 @{" makewhatis.pl invocation   " link "makewhatis.pl invocation"}  Invocation and examples.
 @{" whatis.db file             " link "whatis.db file"}  Format and contents.


@endnode

@node "makewhatis.pl options" "manutils.guide/makewhatis.pl options"
@next "makewhatis.pl invocation"
@toc "Whatis database"

@{b}makewhatis.pl@{ub} options
=====================

   The @{b}makewhatis.pl@{ub} perl script supports the following options.

@{b}-a@{ub}
@{b}-append@{ub}
     Append mode. Don't delete old entries in whatis database.  The new
     database will be sorted without repeated lines and @{b}makewhatis.pl@{ub}
     does not check if old entries are valid.

@{b}-h@{ub}
@{b}-help@{ub}
     Print options and exit.

@{b}-i column@{ub}
@{b}-indent column@{ub}
     Justify description strings to @{b}column@{ub} (default 24).

@{b}-n name@{ub}
@{b}-name name@{ub}
     Use @{b}name@{ub} instead of @{b}whatis@{ub}.

@{b}-o file@{ub}
@{b}-outfile file@{ub}
     Write all output to @{b}file@{ub} instead of dirname/whatis.

@{b}-v@{ub}
@{b}-verbose@{ub}
     Issue more warnings (to stderr). For every parsed man page write a
     single char: @{b}.@{ub} for an uncompressed page, @{b}*@{ub} for a compressed page,
     and @{b}+@{ub} for a link.


@endnode

@node "makewhatis.pl invocation" "manutils.guide/makewhatis.pl invocation"
@next "whatis.db file"
@prev "makewhatis.pl options"
@toc "Whatis database"

@{b}makewhatis.pl@{ub} invocation
========================

   Synopsis:
     makewhatis.pl [-a|-append ] [-h|-help] [-i|-indent column]
     		 [-n|-name name] [-o|-outfile file] [-v|-verbose]
     		 [directories ...]

   Colons are treated as spaces, hence
     makewhatis.pl $MANPATH
   or
     makewhatis.pl `manpath`
   are allowed.

     makewhatis.pl $MANPATH
   Create whatis database for all directories in your @{b}$MANPATH@{ub}.

     makewhatis.pl -outfile /tmp/mywhatis /usr/local/man $HOME/man
   Create whatis database @{b}/tmp/mywhatis@{ub}. Traverse directories
@{b}/usr/local/man@{ub} and @{b}$HOME/man@{ub}. Don't create @{b}/usr/local/man/whatis@{ub} or
@{b}$HOME/man/whatis@{ub}.

     makewhatis.pl -name windex $HOME/man
   Create whatis database @{b}windex@{ub} instead of @{b}whatis@{ub}.  This is useful for
SysV systems.

   Typical usage in the Geek Gadgets environment:
     makewhatis.pl -o /gg/man/whatis.db /gg/man


@endnode

