Preformat man pages
*******************

   The @{b}catman.pl@{ub} perl script is used to create compressed, formatted
man pages from man pages in @{b}nroff@{ub} format.


 @{" catman.pl options    " link "catman.pl options"}  Options for catman.pl.
 @{" catman.pl invocation " link "catman.pl invocation"}  Invocation and examples.


@endnode

@node "catman.pl options" "manutils.guide/catman.pl options"
@next "catman.pl invocation"
@toc "Preformat man pages"

@{b}catman.pl@{ub} options
=================

   The @{b}catman.pl@{ub} perl script supports the following options.

@{b}-f@{ub}
@{b}-force@{ub}
     Force overwriting old cat pages. Normally only those pages will be
     formatted which are not up to date. This option is a waste of
     time, CPU and RAM.

@{b}-h@{ub}
@{b}-help@{ub}
     Print options and exit.

@{b}-p@{ub}
@{b}-print@{ub}
     Don't actually format man pages. Show what would be done.

@{b}-r@{ub}
@{b}-remove@{ub}
     Remove garbage, e.g. catpage without manpage, uncompressed catpage
     but a compressed catpage exists, filenames with non-alphanumeric
     characters, uncompressed manpage but a compressed manpage exists.

@{b}-v@{ub}
@{b}-verbose@{ub}
     More warnings.


@endnode

@node "catman.pl invocation" "manutils.guide/catman.pl invocation"
@prev "catman.pl options"
@toc "Preformat man pages"

@{b}catman.pl@{ub} invocation
====================

@{b}   Catman.pl@{ub} preformats and compresses man pages.

   Synopsis:
     catman.pl [-h|-help] [-f|-force] [-p|-print] [-r|remove]
               [-v|-verbose] [directories ...]

   Typical usage:
     $ catman.pl
   Format man pages in @{b}/usr/share/man@{ub} (default) if neccessary.

     $ catman.pl $MANPATH
   Format all your man pages if neccessary.

     $ catman.pl -f /usr/local/man/man1 /usr/local/man/manl
   Force reformatting of all man pages in @{b}/usr/local/man/man1@{ub} and
@{b}/usr/local/man/manl@{ub}.

     $ catman.pl -p /usr/X11/man
   Show only.

     $ catman.pl /gg/man
   Format all man pages in @{b}/GG/man@{ub}.


@endnode

