@node "man options" "manutils.guide/man options"
@next "man invocation"
@toc "Display online manuals"

@{b}man@{ub} options
===========

   The @{b}man@{ub} program supports the following options.

@{b}-a@{ub}
@{b}--all@{ub}
     Display all of the manual pages for a specified section and name
     combination. Normally, only the first manual page found is
     displayed.

@{b}-C@{ub}
@{b}--config=FILE@{ub}
     Use the specified file instead of the default configuration file.
     This permits users to configure their own manual environment.  See
     the Configuration chapter for a description of the contents of
     this file.

@{b}-c@{ub}
@{b}--cat@{ub}
     Copy the manual page to the standard output instead of using the
     default pager to paginate it. This is done by default if the
     standard output is not a terminal device.

@{b}-h@{ub}
@{b}--header@{ub}
     Display only the @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub} lines of the requested manual pages.

@{b}-M@{ub}
@{b}--manpath=LIST@{ub}
     Override the list of standard directories which @{b}man@{ub} searches for
     manual pages. The supplied path must be a colon @{b}:@{ub} separated list
     of directories. This search path may also be set using the
     environment variable @{b}MANPATH@{ub}. The subdirectories to be searched,
     and their search order, is specified by the @{b}_subdir@{ub} line in the
     @{b}man@{ub} configuration file.

@{b}-m@{ub}
@{b}--augment=LIST@{ub}
     Augment the list of standard directories which @{b}man@{ub} searches for
     manual pages. The supplied path must be a colon @{b}:@{ub} separated list
     of directories. These directories will be searched before the
     standard directories or the directories specified using the @{b}-M@{ub}
     option or the @{b}MANPATH@{ub} environment variable. The subdirectories to
     be searched, and their search order, is specified by the @{b}_subdir@{ub}
     line in the @{b}man@{ub} configuration file.

@{b}-u@{ub}
@{b}--update@{ub}
     Forces @{b}man@{ub} to update the formatted manual page if either no
     formatted page exists, or if the corresponding unformatted page is
     newer. If this option is used, there is no need to run the
     @{b}catman.pl@{ub} perl script.

@{b}-w@{ub}
@{b}--where@{ub}
     List the pathnames of the manual pages which @{b}man@{ub} would display for
     the specified section and name combination.


@endnode

@node "man invocation" "manutils.guide/man invocation"
@prev "man options"
@toc "Display online manuals"

@{b}man@{ub} invocation
==============

   Synopsis:
     man [OPTIONS]... [SECTION] [KEYWORD]...

     man 5 man.conf
   Show the man.conf manual page from section 5.

     man -k chown
   Print out all one-line summaries matching @{b}chown@{ub} from the whatis
database.

     man -M /usr/man ls
   Show the man page for ls located in /usr/man.


